eur = Thomas the Imposter", "work_id": 116100, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T13:40:24.297212+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "faf94c11-65de-447d-b9bb-fb9fb9c5446a", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "30940", "external_references": [{"id": 39593, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121144191"}], "date_modified": "2025-05-22T23:00:31.779111+10:00"}, {"id": 83055, "name": "Christian-Jaque", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 3104553, "title": "La Chartreuse de Parme = the Charterhouse of Parma", "work_id": 115971, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "Christian Albert François Maudet", "date_of_birth": "04 SEP 1904", "date_of_death": "08 JUL 1994", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 4, "name": "French", "slug": "french"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 17, "name": "France", "slug": "france"}], "biography": "Christian-Jaque (byname of Christian Maudet; 4 September 1904  – 8 July 1994) was a French filmmaker. From 1954 to 1959, he was married to actress Martine Carol, who starred in several of his films, including Lucrèce Borgia (1953), Madame du Barry (1954), and Nana (1955).\nChristian-Jaque's 1946 film A Lover's Return was entered into the 1946 Cannes Film Festival.\nHe won the Best Director award at the 1952 Cannes Film Festival for his popular swashbuckler Fanfan la Tulipe.  At the 2nd Berlin International Film Festival, he won the Silver Bear award  for the same film. In 1959, he was a member of the jury at the 1st Moscow International Film Festival.Christian-Jaque began his motion picture career in the 1920s as an art director and production designer.  By the early 1930s, he had moved into screenwriting and directing.  He continued working into the mid-1980s, though from 1970 on, most of his work was done for television. In 1979, he was a member of the jury at the 11th Moscow International Film Festival.Christian-Jaque was born in Paris.  He died at Boulogne-Billancourt in 1994.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-06T10:38:17.062702+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 1815, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christian-Jaque"}], "uuid": "a323e524-5905-4d03-bdb3-433ba5cc85bd", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "30937", "external_references": [{"id": 7904, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q728214"}, {"id": 7905, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "14828105"}, {"id": 7906, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "nb2001048835"}, {"id": 7907, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-nb2001048835"}], "date_modified": "2025-05-22T22:42:12.471152+10:00"}, {"id": 83054, "name": "Jean-Gabriel Albicocco", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 3104547, "title": "Le Rat D'amerique = the Rat Trap", "work_id": 115968, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1936-02-15", "date_of_death": "2001-04-10", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 4, "name": "French", "slug": "french"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 17, "name": "France", "slug": "france"}], "biography": "Jean-Gabriel Albicocco (15 February 1936, Cannes – 10 April 2001, Rio de Janeiro) was a French film director.\nIn 1960 he married French actress and singer Marie Laforêt. He is considered a figure of the French New Wave cinema or Nouvelle Vague.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-05T21:11:31.427262+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2335, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean-Gabriel_Albicocco"